This paper focuses on natural language processing (NLP) tasks, specifically named entity recognition (NER), which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of neural networks, specifically BiLSTM, which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of self-attention, which is a technique commonly used in neural networks for various tasks, including NLP (cs.NE). Finally, the paper mentions the use of real-world datasets, which may involve computer vision techniques (cs.CV) for image recognition or processing.
